32// `OperationBuffer` is a growable, Zone-allocated buffer to store Turboshaft
33// operations. It is part of a `Graph`.
34// The buffer can be seen as an array of 8-byte `OperationStorageSlot` values.
35// The structure is append-only, that is, we only add operations at the end.
36// There are rare cases (i.e., loop phis) where we overwrite an existing
37// operation, but only if we can guarantee that the new operation is not bigger
38// than the operation we overwrite.
39class OperationBuffer {
40 public:
41 // A `ReplaceScope` is to overwrite an existing operation.
42 // It moves the end-pointer temporarily so that the next emitted operation
43 // overwrites an old one.
44 class ReplaceScope {
45 public:
46 ReplaceScope(OperationBuffer* buffer, OpIndex replaced)
47 : buffer_(buffer),
48 replaced_(replaced),
49 old_end_(buffer->end_),
50 old_slot_count_(buffer->SlotCount(replaced)) {
51 buffer_->end_ = buffer_->Get(replaced);
52 }
53 ~ReplaceScope() {
54 DCHECK_LE(buffer_->SlotCount(replaced_), old_slot_count_);
55 buffer_->end_ = old_end_;
56 // Preserve the original operation size in case it has become smaller.
57 buffer_->operation_sizes_[replaced_.id()] = old_slot_count_;
58 buffer_->operation_sizes_[OpIndex(replaced_.offset() +
59 static_cast<uint32_t>(old_slot_count_) *
60 sizeof(OperationStorageSlot))
61 .id() -
62 1] = old_slot_count_;
63 }
64
65 ReplaceScope(const ReplaceScope&) = delete;
66 ReplaceScope& operator=(const ReplaceScope&) = delete;
67
68 private:
69 OperationBuffer* buffer_;
70 OpIndex replaced_;
71 OperationStorageSlot* old_end_;
72 uint16_t old_slot_count_;
73 };
74
75 explicit OperationBuffer(Zone* zone, size_t initial_capacity) : zone_(zone) {
76 DCHECK_NE(initial_capacity, 0);
77 begin_ = end_ =
78 zone_->AllocateArray<OperationStorageSlot>(initial_capacity);
79 operation_sizes_ =
80 zone_->AllocateArray<uint16_t>((initial_capacity + 1) / kSlotsPerId);
81 end_cap_ = begin_ + initial_capacity;
82 }
83
84 OperationStorageSlot* Allocate(size_t slot_count) {
85 if (V8_UNLIKELY(static_cast<size_t>(end_cap_ - end_) < slot_count)) {
86 Grow(capacity() + slot_count);
87 DCHECK(slot_count <= static_cast<size_t>(end_cap_ - end_));
88 }
89 OperationStorageSlot* result = end_;
90 end_ += slot_count;
91 OpIndex idx = Index(result);
92 // Store the size in both for the first and last id corresponding to the new
93 // operation. This enables iteration in both directions. The two id's are
94 // the same if the operation is small.
95 operation_sizes_[idx.id()] = slot_count;
96 operation_sizes_[OpIndex(idx.offset() + static_cast<uint32_t>(slot_count) *
97 sizeof(OperationStorageSlot))
98 .id() -
99 1] = slot_count;
100 return result;
101 }
102
103 void RemoveLast() {
104 size_t slot_count = operation_sizes_[EndIndex().id() - 1];
105 end_ -= slot_count;
106 DCHECK_GE(end_, begin_);
107 }
108
109 OpIndex Index(const Operation& op) const {
110 return Index(reinterpret_cast<const OperationStorageSlot*>(&op));
111 }
112 OpIndex Index(const OperationStorageSlot* ptr) const {
113 DCHECK(begin_ <= ptr && ptr <= end_);
114 return OpIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(ptr) -
115 reinterpret_cast<Address>(begin_)));
116 }
117
118 OperationStorageSlot* Get(OpIndex idx) {
119 DCHECK_LT(idx.offset() / sizeof(OperationStorageSlot), size());
120 return reinterpret_cast<OperationStorageSlot*>(
121 reinterpret_cast<Address>(begin_) + idx.offset());
122 }
123 uint16_t SlotCount(OpIndex idx) {
124 DCHECK_LT(idx.offset() / sizeof(OperationStorageSlot), size());
125 return operation_sizes_[idx.id()];
126 }
127
128 const OperationStorageSlot* Get(OpIndex idx) const {
129 DCHECK_LT(idx.offset(), capacity() * sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
130 return reinterpret_cast<const OperationStorageSlot*>(
131 reinterpret_cast<Address>(begin_) + idx.offset());
132 }
133
134 OpIndex Next(OpIndex idx) const {
135 DCHECK_GT(operation_sizes_[idx.id()], 0);
136 OpIndex result = OpIndex(idx.offset() + operation_sizes_[idx.id()] *
137 sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
138 DCHECK_LT(0, result.offset());
139 DCHECK_LE(result.offset(), capacity() * sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
140 return result;
141 }
142 OpIndex Previous(OpIndex idx) const {
143 DCHECK_GT(idx.id(), 0);
144 DCHECK_GT(operation_sizes_[idx.id() - 1], 0);
145 OpIndex result = OpIndex(idx.offset() - operation_sizes_[idx.id() - 1] *
146 sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
147 DCHECK_LE(0, result.offset());
148 DCHECK_LT(result.offset(), capacity() * sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
149 return result;
150 }
151
152 // Offset of the first operation.
153 OpIndex BeginIndex() const { return OpIndex(0); }
154 // One-past-the-end offset.
155 OpIndex EndIndex() const { return Index(end_); }
156
157 uint32_t size() const { return static_cast<uint32_t>(end_ - begin_); }
158 uint32_t capacity() const { return static_cast<uint32_t>(end_cap_ - begin_); }
159
160 void Grow(size_t min_capacity) {
161 size_t size = this->size();
162 size_t capacity = this->capacity();
163 size_t new_capacity = 2 * capacity;
164 while (new_capacity < min_capacity) new_capacity *= 2;
165 CHECK_LT(new_capacity, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() /
166 sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
167
168 OperationStorageSlot* new_buffer =
169 zone_->AllocateArray<OperationStorageSlot>(new_capacity);
170 memcpy(new_buffer, begin_, size * sizeof(OperationStorageSlot));
171
172 uint16_t* new_operation_sizes =
173 zone_->AllocateArray<uint16_t>(new_capacity / kSlotsPerId);
174 memcpy(new_operation_sizes, operation_sizes_,
175 size / kSlotsPerId * sizeof(uint16_t));
176
177 begin_ = new_buffer;
178 end_ = new_buffer + size;
179 end_cap_ = new_buffer + new_capacity;
180 operation_sizes_ = new_operation_sizes;
181 }
182
183 void Reset() { end_ = begin_; }
184
185 private:
186 Zone* zone_;
187 OperationStorageSlot* begin_;
188 OperationStorageSlot* end_;
189 OperationStorageSlot* end_cap_;
190 uint16_t* operation_sizes_;
191};

193template <class Derived>
194class DominatorForwardTreeNode;
195template <class Derived>
196class RandomAccessStackDominatorNode;
197
198template <class Derived>
199class DominatorForwardTreeNode {
200 // A class storing a forward representation of the dominator tree, since the
201 // regular dominator tree is represented as pointers from the children to
202 // parents rather than parents to children.
203 public:
204 void AddChild(Derived* next) {
205 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<Derived*>(this)->len_ + 1, next->len_);
206 next->neighboring_child_ = last_child_;
207 last_child_ = next;
208 }
209
210 Derived* LastChild() const { return last_child_; }
211 Derived* NeighboringChild() const { return neighboring_child_; }
212 bool HasChildren() const { return last_child_ != nullptr; }
213
214 base::SmallVector<Derived*, 8> Children() const {
215 base::SmallVector<Derived*, 8> result;
216 for (Derived* child = last_child_; child != nullptr;
217 child = child->neighboring_child_) {
218 result.push_back(child);
219 }
220 std::reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
221 return result;
222 }
223
224 private:
225#ifdef DEBUG
226 friend class RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>;
227#endif
228 Derived* neighboring_child_ = nullptr;
229 Derived* last_child_ = nullptr;
230};
231
232template <class Derived>
233class RandomAccessStackDominatorNode
234 : public DominatorForwardTreeNode<Derived> {
235 // This class represents a node of a dominator tree implemented using Myers'
236 // Random-Access Stack (see
237 // https://publications.mpi-cbg.de/Myers_1983_6328.pdf). This datastructure
238 // enables searching for a predecessor of a node in log(h) time, where h is
239 // the height of the dominator tree.
240 public:
241 void SetDominator(Derived* dominator);
242 void SetAsDominatorRoot();
243 Derived* GetDominator() const { return nxt_; }
244
245 // Returns the lowest common dominator of {this} and {other}.
246 Derived* GetCommonDominator(
247 RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>* other) const;
248
249 bool IsDominatedBy(const Derived* other) const {
250 // TODO(dmercadier): we don't have to call GetCommonDominator and could
251 // determine quicker that {this} isn't dominated by {other}.
252 return GetCommonDominator(other) == other;
253 }
254
255 int Depth() const { return len_; }
256
257 private:
258 friend class DominatorForwardTreeNode<Derived>;
259#ifdef DEBUG
260 friend class Block;
261#endif
262
263 // Myers' original datastructure requires to often check jmp_->len_, which is
264 // not so great on modern computers (memory access, caches & co). To speed up
265 // things a bit, we store here jmp_len_.
266 int jmp_len_ = 0;
267
268 int len_ = 0;
269 Derived* nxt_ = nullptr;
270 Derived* jmp_ = nullptr;
271};

273// A simple iterator to walk over the predecessors of a block. Note that the
274// iteration order is reversed.
275class PredecessorIterator {
276 public:
277 explicit PredecessorIterator(const Block* block) : current_(block) {}
278
279 PredecessorIterator& operator++();
280 constexpr bool operator==(const PredecessorIterator& other) const {
281 return current_ == other.current_;
282 }
283 constexpr bool operator!=(const PredecessorIterator& other) const {
284 return !(*this == other);
285 }
286
287 const Block* operator*() const { return current_; }
288
289 private:
290 const Block* current_;
291};

298 PredecessorIterator begin() const { return PredecessorIterator(begin_); }
299 PredecessorIterator end() const { return PredecessorIterator(nullptr); }

301 private:

303};

305// A basic block
306class Block : public RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Block> {
307 public:
308 enum class Kind : uint8_t { kMerge, kLoopHeader, kBranchTarget };
309
310 explicit Block(Kind kind) : kind_(kind) {}
311
312 bool IsLoopOrMerge() const { return IsLoop() || IsMerge(); }
313 bool IsLoop() const { return kind_ == Kind::kLoopHeader; }
314 bool IsMerge() const { return kind_ == Kind::kMerge; }
315 bool IsBranchTarget() const { return kind_ == Kind::kBranchTarget; }
316
317 Kind kind() const { return kind_; }
318 void SetKind(Kind kind) { kind_ = kind; }
319
320 BlockIndex index() const { return index_; }
321
322 bool Contains(OpIndex op_idx) const {
323 return begin_ <= op_idx && op_idx < end_;
324 }
325
326 bool IsBound() const { return index_ != BlockIndex::Invalid(); }
327
328 base::SmallVector<Block*, 8> Predecessors() const {
329 base::SmallVector<Block*, 8> result;
330 for (Block* pred = last_predecessor_; pred != nullptr;
331 pred = pred->neighboring_predecessor_) {
332 result.push_back(pred);
333 }
334 std::reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
335 return result;
336 }
337
338 // Returns an iterable object (defining begin() and end()) to iterate over the
339 // block's predecessors.
340 NeighboringPredecessorIterable PredecessorsIterable() const {
341 return NeighboringPredecessorIterable(last_predecessor_);
342 }
343
344 int PredecessorCount() const {
345#ifdef DEBUG
346 CheckPredecessorCount();
347#endif
348 return predecessor_count_;
349 }
350
351#ifdef DEBUG
352 // Checks that the {predecessor_count_} is equal to the number of predecessors
353 // reachable through {last_predecessor_}.
354 void CheckPredecessorCount() const {
355 int count = 0;
356 for (Block* pred = last_predecessor_; pred != nullptr;
357 pred = pred->neighboring_predecessor_) {
358 count++;
359 }
360 DCHECK_EQ(count, predecessor_count_);
361 }
362#endif
363
364 // Returns the index of {target} in the predecessors of the current Block.
365 // If {target} is not a direct predecessor, returns -1.
366 int GetPredecessorIndex(const Block* target) const {
367 int pred_count = 0;
368 int pred_reverse_index = -1;
369 for (Block* pred = last_predecessor_; pred != nullptr;
370 pred = pred->neighboring_predecessor_) {
371 if (pred == target) {
372 DCHECK_EQ(pred_reverse_index, -1);
373 pred_reverse_index = pred_count;
374 }
375 pred_count++;
376 }
377 if (pred_reverse_index == -1) {
378 return -1;
379 }
380 return pred_count - pred_reverse_index - 1;
381 }
382
383 Block* LastPredecessor() const { return last_predecessor_; }
384 Block* NeighboringPredecessor() const { return neighboring_predecessor_; }
385 bool HasPredecessors() const {
386 DCHECK_EQ(predecessor_count_ == 0, last_predecessor_ == nullptr);
387 return last_predecessor_ != nullptr;
388 }
389 void ResetLastPredecessor() {
390 last_predecessor_ = nullptr;
391 predecessor_count_ = 0;
392 }
393
394 // The block from the previous graph which produced the current block. This
395 // has to be updated to be the last block that contributed operations to the
396 // current block to ensure that phi nodes are created correctly.
397 void SetOrigin(const Block* origin) {
398 DCHECK_IMPLIES(origin != nullptr,
399 origin->graph_generation_ + 1 == graph_generation_);
400 origin_ = origin;
401 }
402 // The block from the input graph that is equivalent as a predecessor. It is
403 // only available for bound blocks and it does *not* refer to an equivalent
404 // block as a branch destination.
405 const Block* OriginForBlockEnd() const {
406 DCHECK(IsBound());
407 return origin_;
408 }
409
410 bool IsComplete() const { return end_.valid(); }
411 OpIndex begin() const {
412 DCHECK(begin_.valid());
413 return begin_;
414 }
415 OpIndex end() const {
416 DCHECK(end_.valid());
417 return end_;
418 }
419
420 // Returns an approximation of the number of operations contained in this
421 // block, by counting how many slots it contains. Depending on the size of the
422 // operations it contains, this could be exactly how many operations it
423 // contains, or it could be less.
424 int OpCountUpperBound() const { return end().id() - begin().id(); }
425
426 const Operation& FirstOperation(const Graph& graph) const;
427 const Operation& LastOperation(const Graph& graph) const;
428
429 bool EndsWithBranchingOp(const Graph& graph) const {
430 switch (LastOperation(graph).opcode) {
431 case Opcode::kBranch:
432 case Opcode::kSwitch:
433 case Opcode::kCheckException:
434 return true;
435 default:
436 DCHECK_LE(SuccessorBlocks(*this, graph).size(), 1);
437 return false;
438 }
439 }
440
441 bool HasPhis(const Graph& graph) const;
442
443 bool HasBackedge(const Graph& graph) const {
444 if (const GotoOp* gto = LastOperation(graph).TryCast<GotoOp>()) {
445 return gto->destination->index().id() <= index().id();
446 }
447 return false;
448 }
449
450#ifdef DEBUG
451 // {has_peeled_iteration_} is currently only updated for loops peeled in
452 // Turboshaft (it is true only for loop headers of loops that have had their
453 // first iteration peeled). So be aware that while Turbofan loop peeling is
454 // enabled, this is not a reliable way to check if a loop has a peeled
455 // iteration.
456 bool has_peeled_iteration() const {
457 DCHECK(IsLoop());
458 return has_peeled_iteration_;
459 }
460 void set_has_peeled_iteration() {
461 DCHECK(IsLoop());
462 has_peeled_iteration_ = true;
463 }
464#endif
465
466 // Computes the dominators of the this block, assuming that the dominators of
467 // its predecessors are already computed. Returns the depth of the current
468 // block in the dominator tree.
469 uint32_t ComputeDominator();
470
471 void PrintDominatorTree(
472 std::vector<const char*> tree_symbols = std::vector<const char*>(),
473 bool has_next = false) const;
474
475 enum class CustomDataKind {
476 kUnset, // No custom data has been set for this block.
477 kPhiInputIndex,
478 kDeferredInSchedule,
479 };
480
481 void set_custom_data(uint32_t data, CustomDataKind kind_for_debug_check) {
482 custom_data_ = data;
483#ifdef DEBUG
484 custom_data_kind_for_debug_check_ = kind_for_debug_check;
485#endif
486 }
487
488 uint32_t get_custom_data(CustomDataKind kind_for_debug_check) const {
489 DCHECK_EQ(custom_data_kind_for_debug_check_, kind_for_debug_check);
490 return custom_data_;
491 }
492
493 void clear_custom_data() {
494 custom_data_ = 0;
495#ifdef DEBUG
496 custom_data_kind_for_debug_check_ = CustomDataKind::kUnset;
497#endif
498 }
499
500 private:
501 // AddPredecessor should never be called directly except from Assembler's
502 // AddPredecessor and SplitEdge methods, which takes care of maintaining
503 // split-edge form.
504 void AddPredecessor(Block* predecessor) {
505 DCHECK(!IsBound() ||
506 (Predecessors().size() == 1 && kind_ == Kind::kLoopHeader));
507 DCHECK_EQ(predecessor->neighboring_predecessor_, nullptr);
508 predecessor->neighboring_predecessor_ = last_predecessor_;
509 last_predecessor_ = predecessor;
510 predecessor_count_++;
511 }
512
513
514 Kind kind_;
515 OpIndex begin_ = OpIndex::Invalid();
516 OpIndex end_ = OpIndex::Invalid();
517 BlockIndex index_ = BlockIndex::Invalid();
518 Block* last_predecessor_ = nullptr;
519 Block* neighboring_predecessor_ = nullptr;
520 uint32_t predecessor_count_ = 0;
521 const Block* origin_ = nullptr;
522 // The {custom_data_} field can be used by algorithms to temporarily store
523 // block-specific data. This field is not preserved when constructing a new
524 // output graph and algorithms cannot rely on this field being properly reset
525 // after previous uses.
526 uint32_t custom_data_ = 0;
527#ifdef DEBUG
528 CustomDataKind custom_data_kind_for_debug_check_ = CustomDataKind::kUnset;
529 size_t graph_generation_ = 0;
530 // True if this is a loop header of a loop with a peeled iteration.
531 bool has_peeled_iteration_ = false;
532#endif
533
534 friend class Graph;
535 template <class Reducers>
536 friend class Assembler;
537 template <class Assembler>
538 friend class GraphVisitor;
539};

549class Graph {
550 public:
551 // A big initial capacity prevents many growing steps. It also makes sense
552 // because the graph and its memory is recycled for following phases.
553 explicit Graph(Zone* graph_zone, size_t initial_capacity = 2048)
554 : operations_(graph_zone, initial_capacity),
555 bound_blocks_(graph_zone),
556 all_blocks_(),
557 op_to_block_(graph_zone, this),
558 block_permutation_(graph_zone),
559 graph_zone_(graph_zone),
560 source_positions_(graph_zone, this),
561 operation_origins_(graph_zone, this),
562 operation_types_(graph_zone, this),
563#ifdef DEBUG
564 block_type_refinement_(graph_zone),
565#endif
566 stack_checks_to_remove_(graph_zone) {
567 }
568
569 // Reset the graph to recycle its memory.
570 void Reset() {
571 operations_.Reset();
572 bound_blocks_.clear();
573 // No need to explicitly reset `all_blocks_`, since we will placement-new
574 // new blocks into it, reusing the already allocated backing storage.
575 next_block_ = 0;
576 op_to_block_.Reset();
577 block_permutation_.clear();
578 source_positions_.Reset();
579 operation_origins_.Reset();
580 operation_types_.Reset();
581 dominator_tree_depth_ = 0;
582#ifdef DEBUG
583 block_type_refinement_.Reset();
584 // Do not reset of graph_created_from_turbofan_ as it is propagated along
585 // the phases.
586#endif
587 }
588
589 V8_INLINE const Operation& Get(OpIndex i) const {
590 DCHECK(i.valid());
591 DCHECK(BelongsToThisGraph(i));
592 // `Operation` contains const fields and can be overwritten with placement
593 // new. Therefore, std::launder is necessary to avoid undefined behavior.
594 const Operation* ptr =
595 std::launder(reinterpret_cast<const Operation*>(operations_.Get(i)));
596 // Detect invalid memory by checking if opcode is valid.
597 DCHECK_LT(OpcodeIndex(ptr->opcode), kNumberOfOpcodes);
598 return *ptr;
599 }
600 V8_INLINE Operation& Get(OpIndex i) {
601 DCHECK(i.valid());
602 DCHECK(BelongsToThisGraph(i));
603 // `Operation` contains const fields and can be overwritten with placement
604 // new. Therefore, std::launder is necessary to avoid undefined behavior.
605 Operation* ptr =
606 std::launder(reinterpret_cast<Operation*>(operations_.Get(i)));
607 // Detect invalid memory by checking if opcode is valid.
608 DCHECK_LT(OpcodeIndex(ptr->opcode), kNumberOfOpcodes);
609 return *ptr;
610 }
611
612 void KillOperation(OpIndex i) { Replace<DeadOp>(i); }
613
614 Block& StartBlock() { return Get(BlockIndex(0)); }
615 const Block& StartBlock() const { return Get(BlockIndex(0)); }
616
617 Block& Get(BlockIndex i) {
618 DCHECK_LT(i.id(), bound_blocks_.size());
619 return *bound_blocks_[i.id()];
620 }
621 const Block& Get(BlockIndex i) const {
622 DCHECK_LT(i.id(), bound_blocks_.size());
623 return *bound_blocks_[i.id()];
624 }
625
626 OpIndex Index(const Operation& op) const {
627 OpIndex result = operations_.Index(op);
628#ifdef DEBUG
629 result.set_generation_mod2(generation_mod2());
630#endif
631 return result;
632 }
633 BlockIndex BlockOf(OpIndex index) const {
634 ZoneVector<Block*>::const_iterator it;
635 if (block_permutation_.empty()) {
636 it = std::upper_bound(
637 bound_blocks_.begin(), bound_blocks_.end(), index,
638 [](OpIndex value, const Block* b) { return value < b->begin_; });
639 DCHECK_NE(it, bound_blocks_.begin());
640 } else {
641 it = std::upper_bound(
642 block_permutation_.begin(), block_permutation_.end(), index,
643 [](OpIndex value, const Block* b) { return value < b->begin_; });
644 DCHECK_NE(it, block_permutation_.begin());
645 }
646 it = std::prev(it);
647 DCHECK((*it)->Contains(index));
648 return (*it)->index();
649 }
650
651 void SetBlockOf(BlockIndex block, OpIndex op) { op_to_block_[op] = block; }
652
653 BlockIndex BlockIndexOf(OpIndex op) const { return op_to_block_[op]; }
654
655 BlockIndex BlockIndexOf(const Operation& op) const {
656 return op_to_block_[Index(op)];
657 }
658
659 OpIndex NextIndex(const OpIndex idx) const {
660 OpIndex next = operations_.Next(idx);
661#ifdef DEBUG
662 next.set_generation_mod2(generation_mod2());
663#endif
664 return next;
665 }
666 OpIndex PreviousIndex(const OpIndex idx) const {
667 OpIndex prev = operations_.Previous(idx);
668#ifdef DEBUG
669 prev.set_generation_mod2(generation_mod2());
670#endif
671 return prev;
672 }
673 OpIndex LastOperation() const {
674 return PreviousIndex(next_operation_index());
675 }
676
677 OperationStorageSlot* Allocate(size_t slot_count) {
678 return operations_.Allocate(slot_count);
679 }
680
681 void RemoveLast() {
682 DecrementInputUses(*AllOperations().rbegin());
683 operations_.RemoveLast();
684#ifdef DEBUG
685 if (v8_flags.turboshaft_trace_emitted) {
686 std::cout << "/!\\ Removed last emitted operation /!\\\n";
687 }
688#endif
689 }
690
691 template <class Op, class... Args>
692 V8_INLINE Op& Add(Args... args) {
693#ifdef DEBUG
694 OpIndex result = next_operation_index();
695#endif // DEBUG
696 Op& op = Op::New(this, args...);
697 IncrementInputUses(op);
698
699 DCHECK_EQ(result, Index(op));
700#ifdef DEBUG
701 for (OpIndex input : op.inputs()) {
702 DCHECK_LT(input, result);
703 DCHECK(BelongsToThisGraph(input));
704 }
705
706 if (v8_flags.turboshaft_trace_emitted) {
707 std::cout << "Emitted: " << result << " => " << op << "\n";
708 }
709
710#endif // DEBUG
711
712 return op;
713 }
714
715 template <class Op, class... Args>
716 void Replace(OpIndex replaced, Args... args) {
717 static_assert((std::is_base_of<Operation, Op>::value));
718 static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible<Op>::value);
719
720 const Operation& old_op = Get(replaced);
721 DecrementInputUses(old_op);
722 auto old_uses = old_op.saturated_use_count;
723 Op* new_op;
724 {
725 OperationBuffer::ReplaceScope replace_scope(&operations_, replaced);
726 new_op = &Op::New(this, args...);
727 }
728 if (!std::is_same_v<Op, DeadOp>) {
729 new_op->saturated_use_count = old_uses;
730 }
731 IncrementInputUses(*new_op);
732 }
733
734 V8_INLINE Block* NewLoopHeader(const Block* origin = nullptr) {
735 return NewBlock(Block::Kind::kLoopHeader, origin);
736 }
737 V8_INLINE Block* NewBlock(const Block* origin = nullptr) {
738 return NewBlock(Block::Kind::kMerge, origin);
739 }
740
741 V8_INLINE Block* NewBlock(Block::Kind kind, const Block* origin = nullptr) {
742 if (V8_UNLIKELY(next_block_ == all_blocks_.size())) {
743 AllocateNewBlocks();
744 }
745 Block* result = all_blocks_[next_block_++];
746 new (result) Block(kind);
747#ifdef DEBUG
748 result->graph_generation_ = generation_;
749#endif
750 result->SetOrigin(origin);
751 return result;
752 }
753
754 V8_INLINE bool Add(Block* block) {
755 DCHECK_EQ(block->graph_generation_, generation_);
756 if (!bound_blocks_.empty() && !block->HasPredecessors()) return false;
757
758 DCHECK(!block->begin_.valid());
759 block->begin_ = next_operation_index();
760 DCHECK_EQ(block->index_, BlockIndex::Invalid());
761 block->index_ = next_block_index();
762 bound_blocks_.push_back(block);
763 uint32_t depth = block->ComputeDominator();
764 dominator_tree_depth_ = std::max<uint32_t>(dominator_tree_depth_, depth);
765
766#ifdef DEBUG
767 if (v8_flags.turboshaft_trace_emitted) {
768 std::cout << "\nBound: " << block->index() << " [predecessors: ";
769 auto preds = block->Predecessors();
770 if (preds.size() >= 1) std::cout << preds[0]->index();
771 for (size_t i = 1; i < preds.size(); i++) {
772 std::cout << ", " << preds[i]->index();
773 }
774 std::cout << "]\n";
775 }
776#endif
777
778 return true;
779 }
780
781 void Finalize(Block* block) {
782 DCHECK(!block->end_.valid());
783 block->end_ = next_operation_index();
784 // Upading mapping from Operations to Blocks for the Operations in {block}.
785 for (const Operation& op : operations(*block)) {
786 SetBlockOf(block->index(), Index(op));
787 }
788 }
789
790 void TurnLoopIntoMerge(Block* loop) {
791 DCHECK(loop->IsLoop());
792 DCHECK_EQ(loop->PredecessorCount(), 1);
793 loop->kind_ = Block::Kind::kMerge;
794 for (Operation& op : operations(*loop)) {
795 if (auto* pending_phi = op.TryCast<PendingLoopPhiOp>()) {
796 Replace<PhiOp>(Index(*pending_phi),
797 base::VectorOf({pending_phi->first()}),
798 pending_phi->rep);
799 }
800 }
801 }

803 OpIndex next_operation_index() const { return EndIndex(); }
804 BlockIndex next_block_index() const {
805 return BlockIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(bound_blocks_.size()));
806 }

808 Block* last_block() { return bound_blocks_.back(); }

816 }

823 }

826 }

1004 void ReorderBlocks(base::Vector<uint32_t> permutation) {
1005 DCHECK_EQ(permutation.size(), bound_blocks_.size());
1006 block_permutation_.resize(bound_blocks_.size());
1007 std::swap(block_permutation_, bound_blocks_);
1008
1009 for (size_t i = 0; i < permutation.size(); ++i) {
1010 DCHECK_LE(0, permutation[i]);
1011 DCHECK_LT(permutation[i], block_permutation_.size());
1012 bound_blocks_[i] = block_permutation_[permutation[i]];
1013 bound_blocks_[i]->index_ = BlockIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(i));
1014 }
1015 }

1017 Graph& GetOrCreateCompanion() {
1018 if (!companion_) {
1019 companion_ = graph_zone_->New<Graph>(graph_zone_, operations_.size());
1020#ifdef DEBUG
1021 companion_->generation_ = generation_ + 1;
1022 if (IsCreatedFromTurbofan()) companion_->SetCreatedFromTurbofan();
1023#endif // DEBUG
1024 }
1025 return *companion_;
1026 }
1027
1028 // Swap the graph with its companion graph to turn the output of one phase
1029 // into the input of the next phase.
1030 void SwapWithCompanion() {
1031 Graph& companion = GetOrCreateCompanion();
1032 std::swap(operations_, companion.operations_);
1033 std::swap(bound_blocks_, companion.bound_blocks_);
1034 std::swap(all_blocks_, companion.all_blocks_);
1035 std::swap(next_block_, companion.next_block_);
1036 std::swap(block_permutation_, companion.block_permutation_);
1037 std::swap(graph_zone_, companion.graph_zone_);
1038 op_to_block_.SwapData(companion.op_to_block_);
1039 source_positions_.SwapData(companion.source_positions_);
1040 operation_origins_.SwapData(companion.operation_origins_);
1041 operation_types_.SwapData(companion.operation_types_);
1042#ifdef DEBUG
1043 std::swap(block_type_refinement_, companion.block_type_refinement_);
1044 // Update generation index.
1045 DCHECK_EQ(generation_ + 1, companion.generation_);
1046 generation_ = companion.generation_++;
1047#endif // DEBUG
1048 // Reseting phase-specific fields.
1049 loop_unrolling_analyzer_ = nullptr;
1050 stack_checks_to_remove_.clear();
1051 }

1097 template <class Op>
1098 void IncrementInputUses(const Op& op) {
1099 for (OpIndex input : op.inputs()) {
1100 // Tuples should never be used as input, except in other tuples (which is
1101 // used for instance in Int64Lowering::LowerCall).
1102 DCHECK_IMPLIES(Get(input).Is<TupleOp>(), op.template Is<TupleOp>());
1103 Get(input).saturated_use_count.Incr();
1104 }
1105 }
1106
1107 template <class Op>
1108 void DecrementInputUses(const Op& op) {
1109 for (OpIndex input : op.inputs()) {
1110 // Tuples should never be used as input, except in other tuples (which is
1111 // used for instance in Int64Lowering::LowerCall).
1112 DCHECK_IMPLIES(Get(input).Is<TupleOp>(), op.template Is<TupleOp>());
1113 Get(input).saturated_use_count.Decr();
1114 }
1115 }
1116
1117 // Allocates pointer-stable storage for new blocks, and pushes the pointers
1118 // to that storage to `bound_blocks_`. Initialization of the blocks is defered
1119 // to when they are actually constructed in `NewBlocks`.
1120 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void AllocateNewBlocks() {
1121 constexpr size_t kMinCapacity = 32;
1122 size_t next_capacity = std::max(kMinCapacity, all_blocks_.size() * 2);
1123 size_t new_block_count = next_capacity - all_blocks_.size();
1124 DCHECK_GT(new_block_count, 0);
1125 base::Vector<Block> block_storage =
1126 graph_zone_->AllocateVector<Block>(new_block_count);
1127 base::Vector<Block*> new_all_blocks =
1128 graph_zone_->AllocateVector<Block*>(next_capacity);
1129 DCHECK_EQ(new_all_blocks.size(), all_blocks_.size() + new_block_count);
1130 std::copy(all_blocks_.begin(), all_blocks_.end(), new_all_blocks.begin());
1131 Block** insert_begin = new_all_blocks.begin() + all_blocks_.size();
1132 DCHECK_EQ(insert_begin + new_block_count, new_all_blocks.end());
1133 for (size_t i = 0; i < new_block_count; ++i) {
1134 insert_begin[i] = &block_storage[i];
1135 }
1136 base::Vector<Block*> old_all_blocks = all_blocks_;
1137 all_blocks_ = new_all_blocks;
1138 if (!old_all_blocks.empty()) {
1139 graph_zone_->DeleteArray(old_all_blocks.data(), old_all_blocks.length());
1140 }
1141
1142 // Eventually most new blocks will be bound anyway, so pre-allocate as well.
1143 DCHECK_LE(bound_blocks_.size(), all_blocks_.size());
1144 bound_blocks_.reserve(all_blocks_.size());
1145 }
1146
1147 OperationBuffer operations_;
1148 ZoneVector<Block*> bound_blocks_;
1149 // The next two fields essentially form a `ZoneVector` but with pointer
1150 // stability for the `Block` elements. That is, `all_blocks_` contains
1151 // pointers to (potentially non-contiguous) Zone-allocated `Block`s.
1152 // Each pointer in `all_blocks_` points to already allocated space, but they
1153 // are only properly value-initialized up to index `next_block_`.
1154 base::Vector<Block*> all_blocks_;
1155 size_t next_block_ = 0;
1156 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<BlockIndex> op_to_block_;
1157 // When `ReorderBlocks` is called, `block_permutation_` contains the original
1158 // order of blocks in order to provide a proper OpIndex->Block mapping for
1159 // `BlockOf`. In non-reordered graphs, this vector is empty.
1160 ZoneVector<Block*> block_permutation_;
1161 Zone* graph_zone_;
1162 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<SourcePosition> source_positions_;
1163 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<OpIndex> operation_origins_;
1164 uint32_t dominator_tree_depth_ = 0;
1165 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<Type> operation_types_;
1166#ifdef DEBUG
1167 GrowingBlockSidetable<TypeRefinements> block_type_refinement_;
1168 bool graph_created_from_turbofan_ = false;
1169#endif
1170
1171 Graph* companion_ = nullptr;
1172#ifdef DEBUG
1173 size_t generation_ = 1;
1174#endif // DEBUG
1175
1176 // Phase specific data.
1177 // For some reducers/phases, we use the graph to pass data around. These data
1178 // should always be invalidated at the end of the graph copy.
1179
1180 LoopUnrollingAnalyzer* loop_unrolling_analyzer_ = nullptr;
1181
1182 // {stack_checks_to_remove_} contains the BlockIndex of loop headers whose
1183 // stack checks should be removed.
1184 // TODO(dmercadier): using the Zone for a resizable structure is not great
1185 // (because it tends to waste memory), but using a newed/malloced structure in
1186 // the Graph means that we have to remember to delete/free it, which isn't
1187 // convenient, because Zone memory typically isn't manually deleted (and the
1188 // Graph thus isn't). Still, it's probably not a big deal, because
1189 // {stack_checks_to_remove_} should never contain more than a handful of
1190 // items, and thus shouldn't waste too much memory.
1191 ZoneAbslFlatHashSet<uint32_t> stack_checks_to_remove_;
1192};

1242
1243inline uint32_t Block::ComputeDominator() {
1244 if (V8_UNLIKELY(LastPredecessor() == nullptr)) {
1245 // If the block has no predecessors, then it's the start block. We create a
1246 // jmp_ edge to itself, so that the SetDominator algorithm does not need a
1247 // special case for when the start block is reached.
1248 SetAsDominatorRoot();
1249 } else {
1250 // If the block has one or more predecessors, the dominator is the lowest
1251 // common ancestor (LCA) of all of the predecessors.
1252
1253 // Note that for BranchTarget, there is a single predecessor. This doesn't
1254 // change the logic: the loop won't be entered, and the first (and only)
1255 // predecessor is set as the dominator.
1256 // Similarly, since we compute dominators on the fly, when we reach a
1257 // kLoopHeader, we haven't visited its body yet, and it should only have one
1258 // predecessor (the backedge is not here yet), which is its dominator.
1259 DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind_ == Block::Kind::kLoopHeader, PredecessorCount() == 1);
1260
1261 Block* dominator = LastPredecessor();
1262 for (Block* pred = dominator->NeighboringPredecessor(); pred != nullptr;
1263 pred = pred->NeighboringPredecessor()) {
1264 dominator = dominator->GetCommonDominator(pred);
1265 }
1266 SetDominator(dominator);
1267 }
1268 DCHECK_NE(jmp_, nullptr);
1269 DCHECK_IMPLIES(nxt_ == nullptr, LastPredecessor() == nullptr);
1270 DCHECK_IMPLIES(len_ == 0, LastPredecessor() == nullptr);
1271 return Depth();
1272}
1273
1274template <class Derived>
1275inline void RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>::SetAsDominatorRoot() {
1276 jmp_ = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
1277 nxt_ = nullptr;
1278 len_ = 0;
1279 jmp_len_ = 0;
1280}
1281
1282template <class Derived>
1283inline void RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>::SetDominator(
1284 Derived* dominator) {
1285 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(dominator);
1286 DCHECK_NULL(static_cast<Block*>(this)->neighboring_child_);
1287 DCHECK_NULL(static_cast<Block*>(this)->last_child_);
1288 // Determining the jmp pointer
1289 Derived* t = dominator->jmp_;
1290 if (dominator->len_ - t->len_ == t->len_ - t->jmp_len_) {
1291 t = t->jmp_;
1292 } else {
1293 t = dominator;
1294 }
1295 // Initializing fields
1296 nxt_ = dominator;
1297 jmp_ = t;
1298 len_ = dominator->len_ + 1;
1299 jmp_len_ = jmp_->len_;
1300 dominator->AddChild(static_cast<Derived*>(this));
1301}
1302
1303template <class Derived>
1304inline Derived* RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>::GetCommonDominator(
1305 RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>* other) const {
1306 const RandomAccessStackDominatorNode* a = this;
1307 const RandomAccessStackDominatorNode* b = other;
1308 if (b->len_ > a->len_) {
1309 // Swapping |a| and |b| so that |a| always has a greater length.
1310 std::swap(a, b);
1311 }
1312 DCHECK_GE(a->len_, 0);
1313 DCHECK_GE(b->len_, 0);
1314
1315 // Going up the dominators of |a| in order to reach the level of |b|.
1316 while (a->len_ != b->len_) {
1317 DCHECK_GE(a->len_, 0);
1318 if (a->jmp_len_ >= b->len_) {
1319 a = a->jmp_;
1320 } else {
1321 a = a->nxt_;
1322 }
1323 }
1324
1325 // Going up the dominators of |a| and |b| simultaneously until |a| == |b|
1326 while (a != b) {
1327 DCHECK_EQ(a->len_, b->len_);
1328 DCHECK_GE(a->len_, 0);
1329 if (a->jmp_ == b->jmp_) {
1330 // We found a common dominator, but we actually want to find the smallest
1331 // one, so we go down in the current subtree.
1332 a = a->nxt_;
1333 b = b->nxt_;
1334 } else {
1335 a = a->jmp_;
1336 b = b->jmp_;
1337 }
1338 }
1339
1340 return static_cast<Derived*>(
1341 const_cast<RandomAccessStackDominatorNode<Derived>*>(a));
